Illustrate the scaling of a container named mysql through Kubernetes (using Minikube)

Written exactly like youâ€™ll perform in lab, from opening terminal â†’ deploying â†’ scaling â†’ verifying.

âš™ï¸ Kubernetes Scaling Example â€“ mysql container
Step-by-Step Practical Execution
ğŸ‘‰ Step 1 â€” Open Terminal

Open your terminal or command prompt.

ğŸ‘‰ Step 2 â€” Start Minikube
minikube start


Wait until cluster starts.

ğŸ‘‰ Step 3 â€” Create a MySQL Deployment
kubectl create deployment mysql --image=mysql:5.7

ğŸ‘‰ Step 4 â€” Verify Deployment Created
kubectl get deployments


Output looks like:

NAME     READY   UP-TO-DATE   AVAILABLE   AGE
mysql    1/1     1            1           10s

ğŸ‘‰ Step 5 â€” Scale MySQL Deployment
kubectl scale deployment mysql --replicas=5

ğŸ‘‰ Step 6 â€” Verify Scaling
kubectl get pods -o wide


Expected:

NAME                     READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE   IP           NODE
mysql-xxxx1              1/1     Running   0          10s   ...
mysql-xxxx2              1/1     Running   0          5s    ...
mysql-xxxx3              1/1     Running   0          5s    ...
mysql-xxxx4              1/1     Running   0          5s    ...
mysql-xxxx5              1/1     Running   0          5s    ...

ğŸ‘‰ Step 7 â€” Show Deployment Details
kubectl describe deployment mysql

ğŸ‘‰ Step 8 â€” Show Scaling in Dashboard (Optional Visual)
minikube dashboard


â†’ Opens GUI showing replica count.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
YAML deployment file for MySQL that you can use directly with Kubernetes, plus exact commands to apply and scale it.

ğŸ“„ MySQL Deployment YAML (mysql-deployment.yaml)
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: mysql
  labels:
    app: mysql
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: mysql
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: mysql
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: mysql
        image: mysql:5.7
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3306
        env:
        - name: MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD
          value: "root"
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: mysql-service
spec:
  selector:
    app: mysql
  ports:
  - protocol: TCP
    port: 3306
    targetPort: 3306
  type: ClusterIP

ğŸ§‘â€ğŸ’» Steps to Apply This YAML
Step 1 â€” Create the file

Open terminal and type:

nano mysql-deployment.yaml


Paste the YAML above
Press:

CTRL + O  â†’ Enter â†’ CTRL + X

Step 2 â€” Apply Deployment
kubectl apply -f mysql-deployment.yaml

Step 3 â€” Verify Deployment
kubectl get deployments
kubectl get pods

ğŸ“ˆ Scaling Using YAML Deployment

Scale to 5 replicas:

kubectl scale deployment mysql --replicas=5


Check result:

kubectl get pods -o wide
